    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offensive engine today is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose elite 80.36 efficiency score makes him the undisputed focal point of the lineup. Facing a favorable park environment against Lambert, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park boost and a +14% platoon edge, effectively neutralizing the mid-tier xERA of the opposing arm. Alongside him, **Jacob Wilson** presents our highest ceiling for stolen bases; his 74.08 score is fueled by a leadoff spot and a 10% park factor that creates a high-leverage opportunity to manufacture runs against Cameron. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** remains a strong play at 60.56, his 14% platoon advantage against Peralta helps him overcome the pitcher's sub-4.00 xERA, solidifying his role in the middle of our order.\n\nEfficiency drops off significantly in the bottom third of our lineup, particularly with **Coby Mayo** (43.81) and **Nasim Nunez** (47.72). While **Nasim Nunez** is primarily rostered for his stolen base utility, the optimizer flagged his 4% boost based on the slow delivery profile of Peralta, providing a marginal floor despite the low batting order spot. The most difficult bench decision involved **Drake Baldwin**, who sits at 54.14; he was considered for the UTIL slot, but we opted for the higher projected production of **Gunnar Henderson**. We are also navigating a light day regarding our bench depth, with **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill** all inactive, and **Luis Robert Jr.** remaining sidelined on the IL. We will be closely monitoring the final lineup for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**; the 71.02 score assumes he holds the #3 spot, but any shift down the order could dampen his output against Ober.",
